narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I think the greatest insight I developed through this course was a stronger ability to analyze older works of literature by taking my time and understanding the importance of the lines written.  Previously, I had a difficult time with material that was not contemporary because it was more difficult to understand, but this course not only introduced me to important older pieces of literature, it allowed me to understand it in both a past and modern context.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think the greatest strength of this course was the professor.  For material that is challenging to read like The Canterbury Tales or Paradise Lost, it's really important to have someone who acknowledges its difficulty and helps their students progress through it; I thought Professor Sheriko did a great job of this.  She also provides really in-depth feedback to essays that helped me to develop a stronger writing style and think more carefully about paragraph placement.  I do not think there were any weaknesses of the course.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, I would absolutely recommend this course to another student.  It was easy to engage with the material because the professor was great and the literature chosen were great representatives of the time and made intellectual stimulation fun and interesting.
